comment: From the legal stand point, WB is being smart. If they were to cancel Johnny Depp because of the allegations and it turns out that the courts find him as the victim the entire time then WB would have a major back blow from fans (worse than what is going on now) and vice versa if they keep Depp and ditch Heard. Not too mention, if WB was to back the wrong person, the other could possibly sue for defamation, ruined career opportunities, etc. From that perspective, WB has 1 of 2 choices, keep both on for their respective projects or ditch both actors. It would be easier for WB to keep both, let them work and then when the trials are done, they can do reshoots for the actor that would be problematic to keep in their movie.
